    },
    {
      "id": 2,
      "text": "Mail service began on July 21, 1868, when the community was still called Boggy, before becoming Niceville a few months later.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        7
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Wikipedia"
      ],
      "source": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Niceville%2C_Florida"
    },
    {
      "id": 3,
      "text": "Every year the Boggy Fest, once the Boggy Bayou Mullet Festival, celebrates local seafood and community spirit in Niceville.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        28
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Wikipedia"
      ],
      "source": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Niceville%2C_Florida"
    },
    {
      "id": 4,
      "text": "Niceville shares a border with Valparaiso, making the two cities twin neighbors on the west side of the county line.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        10
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Wikipedia"
      ],
      "source": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Niceville%2C_Florida"
    },
    {
      "id": 5,
      "text": "The city sits just east of Eglin Air Force Base, with the base’s Boggy Bayou opening into Choctawhatchee Bay nearby.",
